(For educational purposes only) Throwback to when I worked at the animal hospital! HAVE YOU EVER SEEN A UTERUS FILLED WITH PYOMETRA? 
Have you ever heard of Pyometra? 
PYOMETRA is a serious infection in the uterus, causing it to fill with pus, and can lead to other serious conditions including toxaemia, kidney failure, severe dehydration and even death if left untreated. Dogs with PYOMETRA should be spayed and never used as a candidate for breeding! This uterus came from a dog weighing 8pounds! The removed uterus weighed right under 3 pounds!

This poor puppy came to the hospital inside the mouth of another dog! Owners couldn’t get the dog the release it, so they came straight to the animal hospital! Unfortunately this dog had to be put down due to the injuries sustained from their fight!

C section surprise!
This is anasarca also know as Water puppies, walrus puppies, and rubber puppies. Puppies are born with an extreme amount of fluid , edema, under their skin. In severe cases such as this one, puppies typically die shortly after birth.
